title: "The Shape of Discovery: Detecting Topological Precursors to Technological Breakthroughs in the USPTO Patent Citation Network"
abstract: >-
  Applies persistent homology to the U.S. patent citation network (~8M patents,
  ~118M citations, 1976-2023) to test whether topological signatures precede
  technological breakthroughs. After controlling for density confound via scale
  normalization (r=0.970 to r=0.036), all four tests are significant: beta-1
  t-test p=0.023, Wilcoxon p=0.016; persistence entropy t-test p=0.0001,
  Wilcoxon p=0.0014 — all survive Holm-Bonferroni correction. Expanded
  analysis: N=65 curated breakthroughs (57 valid comparisons), all 28 CPC
  pairs cached. Six confound robustness checks implemented (NB04 section 5).
  Pre-breakthrough topology is systematically lower than matched null models.
  Conceptual design, analytical framework, and implementation by Claude
  (Anthropic). Facilitated by Christopher Ortiz.
